Shishkin, who won the Supreme Novice Hurdle at the Cheltenham Festival in March, made a hugely encouraging debut over fences with an easy win at Kempton on Monday. Bookmakers were quick to respond, and Betfair cut the winner into 7-4 from 5-2 for the Arkle Chase at next year’s Festival. The 1-6 market leader for the Racing TV Beginners Chase at the Surrey track never looked in serious danger and jumped superbly on his way to a very easy defeat of Mick Pastor. The four-horse race was marred by a serious injury to the outsider Sangha River, who appeared to stumble after jumping a fence midway through the contest and was quickly pulled up by his rider Aidan Coleman. More to follow …